7 Debugging
***********

With a complex setup it can be come hard to understand why vm-pcrisis
is doing a specific thing.  In order to understand what is going on you
should check the value of the following variables:

   * `vmpc-true-conditions' is the list of true conditions.

   * `vmpc-actions-to-run' is the list of actions to run, i.e. those
     actions mapped by a `vmpc-*-alist'.

   * `vmpc-saved-headers-alist' the value of headers saved for
     substitution.


If you want to check new contions you can run
`vmpc-build-true-conditions-list' interactively.

If you want to check which true conditions are mapped to actions you can
run `vmpc-build-actions-to-run-list' interactively.  True conditions
which are not mapped to an action are silently ignored.

If you want to run new actions you can run `vmpc-read-actions' and
`vmpc-run-actions' interactively.


