8 New In This Version
*********************

Version 0.11:

   * Profiles can now be stored in the BBDB instead of the file
     `vmpc-auto-profiles-file'.  To enable this and migrate your old
     profiles you should call `vmpc-migrate-profiles-to-BBDB' once. A
     backup of your BBDB will be created first as
     `~/.bbdb-vmpc-profile-migration-backup' and your old profiles-file
     will be moved to `~/.vmpc-auto-profiles-migrated-to-BBDB'.

   * Added `vmpc-add-header' which allows to create a header multiple
     times.  This is useful when having more than one FCC header.

   * `vmpc-prompt-for-profile' finds now all profiles, i.e. before it
     stopped at the first match, now it will check all email addresses.


Version 0.10:

   * Added support for a list of actions in `vmpc-prompt-for-profile'.
     Before it was only possible to specify a single action.


Version 0.9:

   * The new maintainer is: Robert Widhopf-Fenk <hack@robf.de>

   * All variables of pcrisis can be customized now.

   * Added new function `vmpc-toggle-no-automorph' to disable automorph
     for the current buffer.

   * `vmpc-prompt-for-profile' checks all relevant headers now and will
     only prompt for a profile if no matches were found.  It also can
     be called interactively to correct a existing profile association.

   * Renamed `vmpc-composition-buffer-function' to
     `vmpc-composition-buffer'.

   * `vmpc-pre-function' and `vmpc-composition-buffer' handle forms
     now, not only a single function which must be quoted.

   * Renamed `vmpc-replies-alist' to `vmpc-reply-alist' and
     `vmpc-forwards-alist' to `vmpc-forward-alist' for consistency.

   * New function `vmpc-true-conditions' to test conditions without
     actually running some actions.

   * New function `vmpc-read-actions' to set actions by hand.

   * `vmpc-build-actions-to-run-list' and `vmpc-run-actions' are
     interactive now.

   * `vmpc-prompt-for-profile' will search all headers for a recipient
     with an associated profile before prompting for one.

   * When calling `vmpc-prompt-for-profile' interactively form a
     composition buffer one will get prompted again for a profile.  This
     allows to easily fix a bad association.

   * The state variables become buffer-local now, which should prevent
     some bugs, i.e. for saved headers.

   * Rewrite of unlispish code.

   * `M-x checkdoc RET'

   * Several bug fixes and enhancements from Robert P. Goldman.

   * Fixes and updates of the info file.


Version 0.85:

   * This version adds `vmpc-resend-alist', which should be especially
     useful for mailing list maintainers who receive bounced non-member
     posts, and anyone else who frequently uses `vm-resend-message'.


Version 0.84:

   * There is now a `vmpc-newmail-alist' in recognition of the fact that
     you *can* actually test for useful criteria (such as what folder
     you are in when you invoke vm-mail) when creating a brand new
     message.

